This paper deals with the problem of finding a maximum number of pairwise-consistent tuples for a relation that violates a set of functional dependencies. This problem is closely related to database theory and data management, which falls under the category of cs.DB. The paper also presents a polynomial-time algorithm for certain fixed relation schemas, which involves computational complexity and algorithms, falling under cs.DS and cs.CC. Additionally, the paper establishes a dichotomy in the complexity of computing a cardinality repair, which involves theoretical computer science and complexity theory, falling under cs.LG and cs.IT.
